## 3. Decisions

### 3a. DECIDED (converged in conversation)

- **D1 — The 5-file model is the target.** One `must-do/` folder, up to five must-do files, one
  owner each. This is the intended design, not something we are introducing.
- **D2 — Two pieces of work, in order:**
  1. **Finish the 5-file consistency fix** — make every gate (summary, evidence, injection)
     operate on **the caller's own must-do file**, not the hardcoded `must-do.md`.
  2. **Add ownership + auto-pack on top** — session claims a must-do file; a new pre-PLAN step
     builds the pack into that file.
- **D3 — Reuse the per-project watcher pool concurrency model.** Do NOT invent a new concurrency
  system. The watcher pool already provides claim-with-lock, owner = session ID, up-to-5-per-project,
  create-the-next-if-yours-is-taken, atomic `mkdir` lock, and stale reaping. Must-do ownership
  binds to it: **`slot-N` ↔ `must-do-N.md`, same owner, same lock, same lifecycle.** One ownership
  system, never two that can disagree.
- **D4 — Raw conversation is captured by a hook copying the actual transcript, not by the agent.**
  The harness already has the literal transcript on disk at
  `…/projects/<proj>/<session-id>.jsonl` and hooks know that path. "Raw form" = a hook copies (a
  slice of) that JSONL into the pack — true raw, zero paraphrase. The agent separately writes the
  compiled `rough-plan.md`. Pack = `raw-conversation.jsonl` (machine-captured) + `rough-plan.md`
  (agent-compiled) + links to grounding files. This mirrors the beast-mode facts-vs-opinion split:
  the machine captures the truth, the model adds its interpretation.
- **D5 — Auto-clear is scoped to the caller's own file only.** A session's pack build clears and
  repopulates ONLY its own must-do file, never a sibling's. (Forced by concurrency; this is what
  makes the destructive "remove all links" safe.)

### 3b. OPEN — needs the user's ✓ or override (the five forks)

> These are written as **recommendations**. They are NOT yet final. Confirm or override each.

- **F1 — Ownership binding.** *Recommended:* per-agent must-do files tied to the watcher claim
  (D3). *Alternative:* must-do ownership as its own separate registry independent of watchers.
- **F2 — Raw capture method.** *Recommended:* hook copies the actual transcript JSONL (true raw).
  *Alternative:* the agent's written-up version of the conversation instead of the literal log.
- **F3 — Auto-clear scope.** *Recommended:* clears only the caller's own file (D5). Confirm this
  matches the mental model of "remove all the links in the current must-do file."
- **F4 — Trigger.** *Recommended:* BOTH — an explicit signal (kill-switch family, e.g. a `/plan`
  token meaning "we're done talking, build the pack") as the normal path, AND a PLAN-entry gate
  that blocks the first PLAN write until a claimed pack exists, as the backstop.
- **F5 — Solo simplification.** *Recommended:* when an agent is provably alone in the folder, it
  keeps using `must-do.md` (no numbering), and only fans out to `must-do-2.md…` under contention,
  to keep the common case clean.
- **F6 — Sequencing.** Should the 5-file consistency cleanup (D2.1) be folded into this same
  plan/sprint, or shipped as its own sprint first before the auto-pack layer? *(raised, undecided)*

